description:
Why doesnt God do something about all the terrible things happening in the world today? Pastor Ted Wilson, president of the General Conference of Seventh-day Adventists, explores this topic, including the harrowing realities of war and violence that have plagued humanity since time immemorial, from the biblical story of Cain and Abel to the heart-wrenching scenes in modern war-torn regions of the world. This thought-provoking discussion raises crucial inquiries: Why does God allow such suffering? What is the nature of the original war that started in heaven with Lucifer's fall? How does this celestial conflict relate to our current struggles on Earth? Join us as we explore these deep questions through the lens of biblical narratives and insights from Ellen Whites 'Patriarchs and Prophets.' This video is an invitation to understand the great controversy between good and evil and find hope amidst the chaos. 

Follow this weekly series with Pastor Ted Wilson to counter the devil's deception with the truth of God. 

 For a detailed look at this fundamental belief, visit https://www.adventist.org/the-great-controversy/.
fulltitle: A Message from Pastor Ted Wilson: Understanding the Big Picture
